author: breser
msg: Cleanup the zlib expansion test (including compiler warnings).
(zlib_expansion_test):  Use types that match zlib's interface instead of
types that may be different sizes on different platforms.  Calculate the
CRC as we do the inflate, this avoids an ugly typecast.  Remove a bunch of
unnecessary typecasts and use the proper format flags.  Avoid pointer
arithmatic when calculating the size of the remaining input for the last
